Content: @Tholin :  I don't know if you have time to do anything with these, but here are layouts for a set-reset flop and a tristate inverter.  I think these two will be sufficient for my needs.

Author: rtimothyedwards_19428
Content: The `invz` cell is the equivalent of the GF 5V 7 track cell of the same name (I changed pin names to match your conventions), and the `dfsrtp` cell is the equivalent of the GF 5V 7 track cell `gf180mcu_fd_sc_mcu7t5v0__dffrsnq_2`.
